writeSnfBeaconPacketWithId

public void writeSnfBeaconPacketWithId(java.lang.String sID_msb,
                                       int sID_lsb,
                                       int txPower,
                                       int sBcnSkip)
Write a sBeacon packet to the sticker Tx power values: - 0 -> use default value of 8bit tx power value - 1 -> -40dBm - 2 -> -20dBm - 3 -> -16dBm - 4 -> -12dBm - 5 -> -8dBm - 6 -> -4dBm - 7 -> 0dBm - 8 -> +4dBm

Parameters:
sID_msb - - not encrypted id for sBeacon
sID_lsb - - encrypted id for sBeacon
txPower - - option to dedicate a specific tx value to the advertisement or use the global tx value
sBcnSkip - - declares how many transmit slot(s) to skip For Example: - 1 sends each slot - 4 will send each fourth slot

setAdvertisementRate

public boolean setAdvertisementRate(float rate_fast,
                                    float rate_slow,
                                    int timeout,
                                    int tx_power)
Set advertisement rate Two rates are support. Rate_fast is configured till timeout after a connection. Rate_slow is configured afterwards Rate values: - 0.1hz to 100hz Timeout values: - Minimum 1s Tx power values: - lowest 4 bits -> 0:-40dBm 1:-20dBm 2:-16dBm 3:-12dBm 4:-8dBm 5:-4dBm 6: 0dBm 7:+4dBm - next 4 bits -> enables channels: 0x10:ch37 0x20:ch38 0x40:ch39

Parameters:
rate_fast - - Fast rate in hz
rate_slow - - Slow rate in hz
timeout - - timeout in seconds before slow rate
tx_power - - 8bits for channel based tx power configuration
Returns:
True for successful. False for failed

setIBeaconAdvertisementDataAtIndex

public boolean setIBeaconAdvertisementDataAtIndex(int atIndex,
                                                  java.lang.String proximityUUID,
                                                  java.lang.String major,
                                                  java.lang.String minor,
                                                  int signal,
                                                  int iBeaconSkip)
Writes iBeacon packet. Sticker will be configured as an iBeacon afterwards. Tx power values: - Starting -40dBm to +4dBm

Parameters:
atIndex - - declared to 3 for iBeacon
proximityUUID - - unique ID for iBeacon
major - - 2 bytes Major ID
minor - - 2 bytes Minor ID
signal - - see tx power values above -> parameter in between -40 and +4
iBeaconSkip - - declares how many transmit slot(s) to skip For Example: - 1 sends each slot - 4 will send each fourth slot
Returns:
True for successful. False if failed

setAdvertisementSettings

public void setAdvertisementSettings(int interval_fast,
                                     int timeout_fast,
                                     int interval,
                                     int timeout_slow,
                                     int interval_slow,
                                     int channel_txpower_noconn,
                                     int channel_txpower_conn)
Set/change Advertisement Settings Timings are in 1.25ms steps For no active connection advertise with following settings: (1) fast for timeout_fast (2) middle till timeout_slow is reached (3) continue with slow For channel_txpower params: lowest 4 bits -> 0:-40dBm 1:-20dBm 2:-16dBm 3:-12dBm 4:-8dBm 5:-4dBm 6: 0dBm 7:+4dBm next 4 bits -> enables channels: 0x10:ch37 0x20:ch38 0x40:ch39 example: 0x76 -> ch37-39 are sending with 0dBm channel + power: high 4 bits: enabled channels(ch37: 0x10, ch38:0x20, ch39:0x40, low 4 bits: tx-power (0: -40dBm,-20dBm,-16dBm,-12dBm,-8dBm,-4dBm,0dBm, 7: 4dBm)

Parameters:
interval_fast - - 1.25ms steps
timeout_fast - - max 3000 in s
interval - - 1.25ms steps
timeout_slow - - min 2000 in s - 0 disables timeout_slow
interval_slow - - 1.25ms steps
channel_txpower_noconn - - set channel_txpower for no connectable advertisement
channel_txpower_conn - - set channel_txpower for connectable advertisement

setAdvertisementData_v2

public boolean setAdvertisementData_v2(byte[] data,
                                       int atIndex,
                                       int intervalSkip,
                                       int hwAddr,
                                       boolean hwAddrPublic,
                                       LeSnfDevice.ADV_TYPE advType,
                                       int txPower,
                                       int dynOfs,
                                       int dynLength,
                                       int kidx,
                                       int encrLength,
                                       int encrOfs,
                                       int rlen)
Declares Advertisement Data to be used Function call necessary after active connection (handleConnect is true) V2 supports more dynamic data

Parameters:
data - - data information
atIndex - - device specific (0 - 3 Ble Specification) / 4 - 5 custom
intervalSkip - - advertisement slot to skip
hwAddr - - in case should transmit with different hwaddresses
hwAddrPublic - - activate hw address
advType - - use ADV_TYPE(Connectable, None_Connectable, Scanable)
txPower - - see below channel_txpower params
dynOfs - - offset index within data where dynamic data start
dynLength - - length off dynamic data array
kidx - - advertisement key index to use for encryption(Advisory Name requires 0x80 index)
encrLength - - amount of data fields to encrypt
encrOfs - - start of index of entire packet( index 7 is start of data field)
rlen - - random length -> amount of data to randomly encrypt For channel_txpower params: lowest 4 bits -> 0:-40dBm 1:-20dBm 2:-16dBm 3:-12dBm 4:-8dBm 5:-4dBm 6: 0dBm 7:+4dBm next 4 bits -> enables channels: 0x10:ch37 0x20:ch38 0x40:ch39 example: 0x76 -> ch37-39 are sending with 0dBm channel + power: high 4 bits: enabled channels(ch37: 0x10, ch38:0x20, ch39:0x40, low 4 bits: tx-power (0: -40dBm,-20dBm,-16dBm,-12dBm,-8dBm,-4dBm,0dBm, 7: 4dBm)

Parameters:

Returns:
true for success. false otherwise
